result.name: Tai Cheong Bakery

reviews.text:
Famous bakery store for “Hong Kong style egg tart”
There are couple flavors for you to choose. I tried these 2 flavors. It’s delicious! The custard is smooth and mild plus it is not too sweet.
Came in here after seeing a large line forming outside. Their egg tarts were good and the wait wasn’t too long. Line moves fast with many customers ordering 4 or more egg tarts at a time.

If I am not wrong, this is the Central main shop (only a few doors away from the original which was given up back in 2005 due to high rent).  Their egg tarts are loved by many and famously by the last British Governor (Chris Patten).  Personally I am not a fan of their crust as I preferred 东興 ones.  The one I just had here in HongKong seems to be different from the one in Singapore as the egg filling here is softer and more runny (which i find nicer than those in Singapore).

Freshly baked egg tarts, rich and smooth filling with a buttery crust! The perfect balance of sweet and savory as well as the contrasting texture of the filling and tart. Other baked goods such as sugar puffs are available too!
Don’t let the long line dissuade you from trying the egg tarts. These are one of the best egg tarts in HK. A bit on the pricey side but worth the extra premium.
